gr::fec_dev::turbo_encoder:
Turbo Encoding class.

A turbo encoder class that simply passes the input to the output. It is meant to allow us to easily use the FEC API encoder and decoder blocks in an application with no coding.
gr::fec_dev::turbo_encoder::make: Build a turbo encoding FEC API object.
gr::fec_dev::turbo_encoder::set_frame_si: Sets the uncoded frame size to . If  is greater than the value given to the constructor, the frame size will be capped by that initial value and this function will return false. Otherwise, it returns true.
gr::fec_dev::turbo_encoder::rate: Returns the coding rate of this encoder (it will always be 1).
gr::fec_dev::turbo_encoder_impl::set_fra: Sets the uncoded frame size to . If  is greater than the value given to the constructor, the frame size will be capped by that initial value and this function will return false. Otherwise, it returns true.
gr::fec_dev::turbo_encoder_impl::rate: Returns the coding rate of this encoder (it will always be 1).
